@dev Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by
 `interfaceId`. See the corresponding
 https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165#how-interfaces-are-identified[EIP section]
 to learn more about how these ids are created.
 This function call must use less than 30 000 gas.

constructor.details: this contract holds balances of all locked collateral & paid back loan prior to their rightful claimsin order for the vault to work it has to have an association with the PWN logic via `.setPWN(PWN.address)`

onERC1155BatchReceived(address,address,u.details: Handles the receipt of a multiple ERC1155 token types. This function is called at the end of a `safeBatchTransferFrom` after the balances have been updated. To accept the transfer(s), this must return `bytes4(keccak256("onERC1155BatchReceived(address,address,uint256[],uint256[],bytes)"))` (i.e. 0xbc197c81, or its own function selector).

params.data: Additional data with no specified format
params.from: The address which previously owned the token
params.ids: An array containing ids of each token being transferred (order and length must match values array)
params.operator: The address which initiated the batch transfer (i.e. msg.sender)
params.values: An array containing amounts of each token being transferred (order and length must match ids array)

onERC1155Received(address,address,uint25.details: Handles the receipt of a single ERC1155 token type. This function is called at the end of a `safeTransferFrom` after the balance has been updated. To accept the transfer, this must return `bytes4(keccak256("onERC1155Received(address,address,uint256,uint256,bytes)"))` (i.e. 0xf23a6e61, or its own function selector).

params.data: Additional data with no specified format
params.from: The address which previously owned the token
params.id: The ID of the token being transferred
params.operator: The address which initiated the transfer (i.e. msg.sender)
params.value: The amount of tokens being transferred

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pull((address,uint8,uint256,uint256),add.details: function pulling an asset FROM the vault, sending to a defined recipientthis is used for unlocking the collateral on revocations & claims or when claiming a paidback loan

params._asset: An asset construct - for definition see { MultiToken.sol }
params._beneficiary: An address of the recipient of the asset - is set in the PWN logic contract

pullProxy((address,uint8,uint256,uint256.details: function pulling an asset FROM a lender, sending to a borrowerthis function assumes prior approval for the asset to be spend by the borrower address

params._asset: An asset construct - for definition see { MultiToken.sol }
params._beneficiary: An address of the recipient of the asset - is set in the PWN logic contract
params._origin: An address of the lender who is providing the loan asset

push((address,uint8,uint256,uint256),add.details: function accessing an asset and pushing it INTO the vaultthe function assumes a prior token approval was made with the PWNVault.address to be approved

params._asset: An asset construct - for definition see { MultiToken.sol }

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setPWN(address).details: An essential setup function. Has to be called once PWN contract was deployed

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`. See the corresponding https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165#how-interfaces-are-identified[EIP section] to learn more about how these ids are created. This function call must use less than 30 000 gas.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
